The article discusses the state of the U.S. economic recovery and the impact of policy measures. It highlights that the U.S. recovery is strong and inflation is coming down, contrary to predictions. The U.S. economy grew by 4.9% in the third quarter and 2.9% over the past year, outperforming expectations and other advanced economies. The article also mentions the strong post-pandemic productivity growth in the U.S., as well as the rebound in labor force participation and improved financial health of American households. The author credits President Biden's economic plan for contributing to the positive outcomes and emphasizes the need for continued assessment of the data to guide future policy decisions.